Callaway Went Thataway is an amiable spoof of early television's "Hopalong Cassidy" craze.

Mike Frye and Deborah Patterson, co-owners of an advertising firm, have a big hit when they recycle some old Western films starring "Smoky" Callaway for a new television audience. Tom Lorrison, the show's sponsor, is eager to make more films, but nobody has seen Smoky in ten years. Under intense pressure to produce the star, Frye hires Smoky's agent, Georgie Markham, to go look for him.
